In work bowl fitted with metal blade, process tomatoes and onion until smooth, about 2 minutes. Place mixture in a deep saucepan. Add tomato paste, corn syrup, vinegar, sugar, salt, onion powder and garlic powder. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until thickened, for 20 minutes. Transfer to a bowl or container and let cool, uncovered, to room temperature. Variation: Combine equal parts Homemade Ketchup and Traditional Mayonnaise for a simple salad dressing.